results.name: Air Jordan 7 Retro PS 'Flint' 2021
results.story: The 2021 edition of the Air Jordan 7 Retro PS ‘Flint’ revives a 2006 colorway for little kids. The outward design is true to the original, featuring an upper that combines grey nubuck with tumbled white leather. ‘Air Jordan’ is embroidered in purple lettering on the signature Air Jordan 7 tongue, connected to a Huarache-like inner sleeve and covered in a unique geometric print. Matching violet accents appear on a Jumpman logo on the lateral collar and a molded ‘23’ on the heel patch.

results.name: New Balance 991 Slam Jam
results.story: Designed in collaboration with the Italian retailer, the Slam Jam x New Balance 991 Made In England ‘Shap Store’ pays tribute a New Balance outlet store located near the brand’s renowned Flimby factory. The shoe itself features a neutral palette of grey and black, executed on an updated build composed of ripstop nylon with reinforced rubberized overlays at the toe and heel. Pigskin suede is utilized on eyestay and midfoot overlay, the latter accented with reflective piping for added visibility. Slam Jam branding adorns the sneaker’s insoles and lace tips.

Jordan 11 Retro Low Legend Blue (PS)
results.story: Built for little kids, the Air Jordan 11 Retro Low PS ‘Legend Blue’ brings back an OG 1996 colorway in low-top form. The upper is constructed from white leather with a tonal patent leather mudguard and powder blue accents inspired by MJ’s alma mater. On the insole, a Jumpman icon is joined by a ‘25’ graphic that marks the shoe’s silver anniversary. Lightweight cushioning is provided by a full-length Phylon midsole, reinforced underfoot by an icy translucent outsole.

Jordan 11 Retro Low Legend Blue (TD)
results.story: The Air Jordan 11 Retro Low TD ‘Legend Blue’ brings the OG colorway to a new generation of Jordan fans. Rendered in low-top form and scaled down to fit tiny feet, the vintage silhouette carries a white synthetic leather upper secured with elastic no-tie laces. An embroidered Jumpman adorns the mesh tongue in a familiar blue shade inspired by MJ’s alma mater. Lightweight cushioning is provided by a foam midsole, reinforced underfoot by an icy translucent outsole.

results.name: Jordan 11 Retro Low Legend Blue
results.story: The Air Jordan 11 Retro Low ‘Legend Blue’ delivers a low-top edition of the OG colorway that Michael Jordan unveiled at the 1996 NBA All-Star Game. The build is faithful to the original mid-top, featuring a white leather upper with a tonal patent leather mudguard and ballistic mesh tongue. A blue embroidered Jumpman at the heel gives the nod to MJ’s alma mater, while a ‘25’ stamped on the sockliner references the 25th anniversary of the shoe’s worldwide debut.

results.name: Concepts x Asia Irving x Kyrie 7 'Horus' Special Box
Daan Van Der Linden x Blazer Court SB 'Baroque Brown'
results.story: Designed in collaboration with the Nike SB team rider, the Daan Van Der Linden x Nike Blazer Court SB ‘Baroque Brown’ gets dressed in a canvas upper inspired by traditional fishing vests. A fish-hook graphic is embroidered on the olive green leather Swoosh, while a custom heel patch displays a rainbow trout alongside Daan Van Der Linden’s name. The low-top is fortified with a tonal ollie patch on the lateral forefoot and mounted atop a contrasting white rubber midsole. Underfoot, a herringbone-tread gum rubber outsole provides optimal grip

results.name: Palace x Classic Clog 'Tan Camo'
results.story: The Palace x Crocs Classic Clog ‘Tan Camo’ delivers the London skate brand’s take on the flexible slip-on silhouette. A desert camouflage print floods the exterior of the Croslite foam build, featuring breathable ventilation ports and a pivoting heel strap for a secure fit. Palace’s signature triangle logo is stamped in yellow on the contoured footbed. Additional branding elements take the form of eleven Jibbitz charms that accompany the limited-edition release.

Jordan 11 Retro Low Legend Blue (GS)
results.story: Built for big kids, the Air Jordan 11 Retro Low GS ‘Legend Blue’ takes its cues from the OG colorway that MJ debuted at the 1996 NBA All-Star Game. Like the original mid-top, this pair features a white leather upper with a tonal patent leather mudguard and breathable mesh tongue. Contrasting pops of Carolina blue land on the tongue and heel, the latter marked with an embroidered Jumpman. Lightweight cushioning is provided by a soft Phylon midsole, reinforced underfoot by an icy translucent outsole.

results.name: Supreme x Air Max 96 'Metallic Silver'
results.story: Bringing back the cult classic running silhouette, Supreme works with Nike on a trio of Air Max 96 colorways. The 'Metallic Silver' iteration features a polished metallic finish applied to the synthetic leather upper, garlanded with reflective piping and fitted with a series of transparent windows that reveal a red Supreme-branded insole. Additional Supreme branding lands on the mesh tongue and a pebbled leather heel overlay. Lightweight cushioning is provided by a midsole packed with visible Max Air units in the heel and forefoot.

results.name: Nike Air Max 96 Supreme Camo
results.story: The Supreme x Nike Air Max 96 ‘Camo’ is drawn from a three-piece set that continues a string of Air Max running collaborations that began in 2016 with the AM98. The retro silhouette makes use of a camo-print leather upper with reflective piping and a dual-branded mesh tongue. Transparent windows on the side panels and toe box reveal a crimson sockliner plastered with an oversized Supreme wordmark. A final Supreme logo hit lands on the heel overlay in metallic silver. The sneaker rides on an olive green midsole with visible Max Air cushioning in the forefoot and heel.

Nike Air Max 96 Supreme Black
results.story: Releasing as part of a three-piece collaboration, the Supreme x Nike Air Max 96 ‘Black’ updates the retro silhouette with a series of transparent windows on the shark-tooth shaped design elements. The rest of the upper is constructed from black leather with reflective piping and a dual-branded mesh tongue. Additional Supreme branding makes its way to the crimson sockliner and a metallic silver plate on the pebbled-leather heel overlay. The retro runner is mounted on a matching black midsole with visible Max Air units in the heel and forefoot.

Jordan 11 Retro Low Bright Citrus (W)
results.story: The women’s Air Jordan 11 Retro Low ‘Bright Citrus’ revives a simplistic two-tone colorway initially released in 2001 and previously reissued in 2015 as a kids’ exclusive. The low-top utilizes a white leather upper with webbing lace loops and a shiny patent leather overlay in a matching white finish. Vibrant orange accents stand out on the sneaker’s branding elements, including an embroidered Jumpman on the heel tab. Lightweight cushioning is provided by a Phylon midsole, reinforced underfoot by a carbon fiber spring plate and a translucent orange rubber outsole.

ZX 0000 Evolution 'A-ZX Series'
results.story: Representing the letter ‘E’ in the 26-part collection, the adidas ZX 0000 Evolution ‘A-ZX Series’ reveals an unreleased prototype design meant to bridge the gap between the brand’s iconic ZX and EQT running franchises. The white textile upper is fortified with tonal synthetic suede overlays and accented with bright blue three-stripes trimmed in fuchsia. The same hues are repeated atop the tongue, featuring embroidered branding that reads ‘adidas Torsion ZX ….’ (the four dots indicating ‘to be continued’).

Sneakersnstuff x Ultra 4D 'Tee Time'
results.story: The Sneakersnstuff x adidas Ultra 4D ‘Tee Time’ revisits a golf-themed collaboration undertaken by the Three Stripes and the Swedish retailer in 2016. This pair features virtually the same upper used on the original UltraBoost ‘Tee Time,’ highlighted by black and white Primeknit construction with mismatched adidas and SNS branding on each tongue and sockliner. Replacing the older shoe’s Boost cushioning is adidas’ revolutionary 4D midsole, painted black and formed with a blend of light, oxygen and liquid resin.

results.name: Nike LeBron 8 V2 Low Miami Nights (2021)
results.story: The 2021 edition of the Nike LeBron 8 V/2 Low Retro ‘Miami Night’ brings back a popular colorway originally released in 2011, coinciding with LeBron James’ first season with the Miami Heat. Inspired by South Beach’s bright neon lights, the Flywire-infused textile upper is tinged in turquoise and coral hues and enlivened with black speckled detailing. The Swoosh is moved back and extends to a spoiler-like loop at the heel, which reveals LeBron’s signature and an embossed mini-Swoosh. Lightweight cushioning is provided by a compression-molded Phylon midsole and a full-length Max Air unit in Solar Red.
